favorites.content: Heedfulness is the path to the Deathless. Heedlessness is the path to death. The heedful die not. The heedless are as if already dead.
favorites.author: The Buddha

favorites.content: Can miles truly separate you from friends... If you want to be with someone you love, aren't you already there?
favorites.author: Richard Bach

favorites.content: The thoughts we choose to think are the tools we use to paint the canvas of our lives.
favorites.author: Louise Hay

history.content: The thoughts we choose to think are the tools we use to paint the canvas of our lives.

history.content: To see things in the seed, that is genius.
history.author: Laozi

history.content: The beginning of wisdom is found in doubting; by doubting we come to the question, and by seeking we may come upon the truth.
history.author: Peter Abelard

history.content: 'As I am, so are these. As are these, so am I.' Drawing the parallel to yourself, neither kill nor get others to kill.
history.author: The Buddha

quotes.content: Stay positive and happy. Work hard and don't give up hope.
quotes.author: Anonymous

quotes.content: Every day may not be good, but there is something good in every day.
quotes.author: Unknown

quotes.content: The only way to do great work is to love what you do.
quotes.author: Steve Jobs
